Slider in UI - how to set handle size? Answered
in Using jQuery UI  •  3 years ago  
I am using the Slider part of the jQuery UI and I'd like to know if there is a way of resizing the handle to a set size? 
 
The jQuery documentation indicates that 'ui-slider-handle' is the CSS class name that should be used to tweak the handle.

However, I have tried to make the handle a fixed size (e.g. 30px wide) using this class but tweaking the CSS seems to have no effect - looking in the JS it seems there is some calculation to produce the handle size and that the handle size is dynamic (based on slider pane contents) - is this the case?

Is there a way to keep the slider working the same way but have a set handle size?
