rdworth
Re: Slider in UI - how to set handle size?
3 years ago
I assume you tried
Copy code
.ui-slider-handle { width: 30px; }

and didn't have any luck because of css specificity. The rule in the slider css is more specific so it wins. You can override it with the same specificity
Copy code
.ui-slider .ui-slider-handle { width: 30px; }

Note also that a slider handle's position is related to its width. A slider handle by default has a width of 1.2em and to center the handle over its position (rather than left-aligning it) it's given a negative left margin of 1/2 that, or -0.6em; So if you want a width of 30px:
Copy code
.ui-slider .ui-slider-handle { width: 30px; margin-left: -15px; }

Example: http://jsbin.com/ejuyi
 
